objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of upadacitinib compared to placebo in subjects with active psoriatic arthritis (PsA) who have had an inadequate response or intolerance to at least 1 bDMARD

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objectives
objectives.text: To evaluate key secondary efficacy endpoints of upadacitinib versus placebo

objectives.name: Safety Objective
objectives.text: Safety evaluations include adverse event (AE) monitoring, physical examinations, vital sign measurements, electrocardiogram (ECG), and clinical laboratory testing (hematology, chemistry, and urinalysis) as a measure of safety and tolerability for the entire study duration.

objectives.name: Pharmacokinetic Objective
objectives.text: Blood samples for assay of upadacitinib and possibly other medications in plasma will be collected at each visit after baseline in Period 1.

objectives.name: Exploratory Research Objective
objectives.text: Prognostic, surrogate, predictive, and pharmacodynamic biomarkers signatures may be evaluated.

endpoints.name: Primary Efficacy Endpoint
endpoints.text: proportion of subjects achieving ACR20 response at Week 12

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 1
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in HAQ-DI at Week 12

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 2
endpoints.text: Static Investigator Global Assessment (sIGA) of Psoriasis of 0 or 1 and at least a 2-point improvement from baseline at Week 16

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 3
endpoints.text: Psoriasis Area Severity Index (PASI) 75 response at Week 16 (for subjects with ≥ 3% BSA psoriasis at baseline)

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 4
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in SF-36 PCS at Week 12

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 5
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in FACIT-Fatigue Questionnaire at Week 12

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 6
endpoints.text: Proportion of subjects achieving Minimal Disease Activity (MDA) at Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 7
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in Self-Assessment of Psoriasis Symptoms (SAPS) Questionnaire at Week 16

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 8
endpoints.text: ACR50/70 response at Week 12

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 9
endpoints.text: ACR20 response at Week 2

endpoints.name: Safety Endpoints
endpoints.text: AEs, physical examination, laboratory assessments, ECG, and vital signs

endpoints.name: Pharmacokinetic Endpoints
endpoints.text: population central values and the empirical Bayesian estimates of the individual values of upadacitinib oral clearance (CL/F) and volume of distribution (V/F)

endpoints.name: Exploratory Endpoints
endpoints.text: nucleic acids, proteins, metabolites, or lipids

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with active PsA and inadequate response or intolerance to at least 1 bDMARD (Full Analysis Set) Summary measure: Difference in proportions (Cochran-Mantel-Haenszel test).

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject discontinues study drug treatment before Week 12

intercurrentEvents.name: Rescue medication use
intercurrentEvents.text: Initiation of rescue therapy for lack of efficacy

estimands.treatment: Upadacitinib (15 mg or 30 mg QD) vs Placebo
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with active PsA and inadequate response or intolerance to at least 1 bDMARD (Full Analysis Set)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Proportion of subjects achieving ACR20 response at Week 12

estimands.name: Secondary Efficacy Estimand - HAQ-DI
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with active PsA and inadequate response or intolerance to at least 1 bDMARD (Full Analysis Set) Summary measure: Difference in least squares means (ANCOVA).

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject discontinues study drug treatment before Week 12

estimands.treatment: Upadacitinib (15 mg or 30 mg QD) vs Placebo
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with active PsA and inadequate response or intolerance to at least 1 bDMARD (Full Analysis Set)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Change from baseline in HAQ-DI at Week 12

estimands.name: Secondary Efficacy Estimand - MDA
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with active PsA and inadequate response or intolerance to at least 1 bDMARD (Full Analysis Set) Summary measure: Difference in proportions (Cochran-Mantel-Haenszel test).

intercurrentEvents.name: Mandatory treatment switch
intercurrentEvents.text: Subjects receiving upadacitinib 30 mg QD switched to 15 mg QD per Protocol Amendment 8

intercurrentEvents.name: Lack of efficacy discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Discontinuation due to failure to demonstrate 20% improvement in TJC/SJC at Week 36

estimands.treatment: Upadacitinib (15 mg or 30 mg QD) vs Placebo
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with active PsA and inadequate response or intolerance to at least 1 bDMARD (Full Analysis Set)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Proportion of subjects achieving Minimal Disease Activity (MDA) at Week 24
